      "cooking_instructions": [
        {
          "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>steak</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it adjust to room temperature</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into<strong> </strong>chips, then add to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
          "order": 1,
          "media": {
            "images": [
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-1-x200.jpg",
                "width": 200
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-1-x400.jpg",
                "width": 400
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-1-x700.jpg",
                "width": 700
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-1-x1000.jpg",
                "width": 1000
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-1-x1500.jpg",
                "width": 1500
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 10-15 min or until softened and caramelised</p><p>While the onions are cooking, strip your <strong>rosemary</strong> from their stems and chop them finely, discard the stems</p>",
          "order": 2,
          "media": {
            "images": [
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-2-x200.jpg",
                "width": 200
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-2-x400.jpg",
                "width": 400
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-2-x700.jpg",
                "width": 700
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-2-x1000.jpg",
                "width": 1000
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-2-x1500.jpg",
                "width": 1500
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "instruction": "<p>Tip: Hold the top of the herb sprigs firmly and slide your fingers down their lengths to easily remove the leaves</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped rosemary</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a small bowl and set aside for later – this is your<strong> rosemary salt</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>wholegrain mustard </strong>(not a big fan of mustard? Go easy!)<strong> </strong>and <strong>mayo </strong>in a separate bowl,<strong> </strong>stir it all together<strong> </strong>and set aside for later – this is your<strong> mustard mayo</strong></p>",
          "order": 3,
          "media": {
            "images": [
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-3-x200.jpg",
                "width": 200
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-3-x400.jpg",
                "width": 400
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-3-x700.jpg",
                "width": 700
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-3-x1000.jpg",
                "width": 1000
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-3-x1500.jpg",
                "width": 1500
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "instruction": "<p>Once the onions are caramelised, add your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min further or until sticky</p><p>Once done, remove the pan from the heat, cover with a lid to keep warm, and set aside for later – these are your <strong>balsamic onions</strong></p>",
          "order": 4,
          "media": {
            "images": [
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-4-x200.jpg",
                "width": 200
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-4-x400.jpg",
                "width": 400
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-4-x700.jpg",
                "width": 700
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-4-x1000.jpg",
                "width": 1000
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-4-x1500.jpg",
                "width": 1500
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the <strong>halved cherry tomatoes</strong> and <strong>salad </strong>to a bowl with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> and gently mix together – this is your <strong>salad</strong></p><p>Pat your <strong>steak[s]</strong> dry with kitchen paper, then drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> on both sides</p>",
          "order": 5,
          "media": {
            "images": [
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-5-x200.jpg",
                "width": 200
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-5-x400.jpg",
                "width": 400
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-5-x700.jpg",
                "width": 700
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-5-x1000.jpg",
                "width": 1000
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-5-x1500.jpg",
                "width": 1500
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat, once very hot, add the<strong> seasoned steak</strong> to the pan</p><p>For rare, cook for 2-3 min max on each side; for medium-rare, cook for 3-4 min on each side; for medium, cook for 4-5 min on each side</p><p>Transfer the<strong> cooked steak </strong>to a clean chopping board, cover with a clean tea towel and leave to rest (save the pan for the next step!)</p>",
          "order": 6,
          "media": {
            "images": [
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-6-x200.jpg",
                "width": 200
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-6-x400.jpg",
                "width": 400
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-6-x700.jpg",
                "width": 700
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-6-x1000.jpg",
                "width": 1000
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-6-x1500.jpg",
                "width": 1500
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "instruction": "<p>While the steak is cooking, cut your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> in half</p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> ciabatta halves </strong>and cook for 1 min on each side, or until golden brown and toasted (the ciabatta will soak up all the juices from the steak for extra flavour!)</p>",
          "order": 7,
          "media": {
            "images": [
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-7-x200.jpg",
                "width": 200
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-7-x400.jpg",
                "width": 400
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-7-x700.jpg",
                "width": 700
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-7-x1000.jpg",
                "width": 1000
              },
              {
                "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2299Step-7-x1500.jpg",
                "width": 1500
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>rested steak </strong>finely</p><p>Divide the <strong>balsamic</strong> <strong>onions</strong> between the<strong> toasted ciabatta halves</strong></p><p>Top with the<strong> sliced</strong> <strong>steak</strong> and drizzle over the <strong>mustard</strong> <strong>mayo </strong>– this is your <strong>open steak sandwich with balsamic onions</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>chips</strong> and <strong>salad</strong> to the side and sprinkle the <strong>rosemary salt </strong>all over the chips</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
          "order": 8,
          "media": {
            "images": []
          }
        }
